
Overview of noun justification

The noun justification has 3 senses (first 2 from tagged texts)
                                  
1. (3) justification -- (something (such as a fact or circumstance) that shows an action to be reasonable or necessary; "he considered misrule a justification for revolution")
2. (2) justification -- (a statement in explanation of some action or belief)
3. justification -- (the act of defending or explaining or making excuses for by reasoning; "the justification of barbarous means by holy ends"- H.J.Muller)
